<HEAD>Reagan Cracks Joke as Balloon Pops</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> was in the midst of his speech to the Republican National Convention Monday night when a balloon popped. `` Missed me,'' he said quickly and went on without a pause. That's become one of his favorite retorts to such sounds. A few moments later, in a series of statements that he began with `` facts are stubborn things,'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> misspoke. `` Facts are stupid things,'' he said and, just as quickly as before, corrected himself to say `` facts are stubborn things.''
