<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Beginning today, anyone who in a year writes three checks that bounce in <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION> will not be allowed to have a bank account for six months. <PERSON> Jaafar </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON>, Governor of <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Negara </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> -RRB-, told reporters that just too many people have been issuing dud checks. Currently, anyone issuing bad checks is fined 100 ringgits -LRB- $ 37 -RRB- per check. `` In a recent survey, the <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banks </ORGANIZATION> In <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION> discovered that every month about 30,000 checks turn up that are n't worth the paper they are printed on, <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Straits </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> in an editorial today
