<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Bennett </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, the esteemed trial lawyer and sports entrepreneur, rarely appeared in court when it was not crowded with fellow attorneys who wanted to see a master at work. `` He was a role model for every honest, tough criminal lawyer in the postwar era,'' said <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Dershowitz </PERSON>, a criminal lawyer and <ORGANIZATION> Harvard </ORGANIZATION> law school professor. Lawyer <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> <PERSON> Clifford </PERSON>, an adviser to presidents, said, `` The bar has lost perhaps its most outstanding advocate.'' EBW, as he was known to his friends and co-workers, died Saturday evening in <LOCATION> Georgetown </LOCATION> <LOCATION> University </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> at age 68 after battling cancer for the past 11 years, undergoing seven operations but returning to work as soon as possible after each one. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Califano </PERSON>, a former law partner and a member of President <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON>'s Cabinet, said, `` He was the best. He was the best everything. He was the best father, the best husband, the best lawyer, the best partner, the best friend ... and he was extraordinarily brave.'' A funeral mass for <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> will be held Tuesday at <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Matthew </LOCATION>'s Cathedral here where he often attended morning mass before he went to work a few blocks away. He made his reputation in the law defending the powerful in their times of greatest need. As a sideline, he also was a one-time president of the <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Redskins </ORGANIZATION> of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Football </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> and the owner of the <ORGANIZATION> Baltimore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Orioles </ORGANIZATION> baseball team at the time of h