'' <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> said. The ceremomy also included liturgies from the Eastern churches, with hymns sung by <LOCATION> Syrian </LOCATION>, Greek, Albanian and Coptic-rite monks. One Ethiopian group chanted African songs to the beat of tribal drums. A group of Sicilian girls in traditional costumes threw thousands of rose petals on an altar representing the tomb of <PERSON> Mary </PERSON>. The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> has said Catholics can gain indulgence, or the pardon of temporal punishment for sin, by devoutly participating in seminars and special pilgrimages to mark the Marian Year. In conjunction with the <PERSON> Marian </PERSON> <PERSON> Year </PERSON>, the pope is scheduled to release in the next few weeks a major document on the role of women in society and the church.
