<HEAD>Humphrey Relishes `Lone Wolf' Role</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By NORMA LOVE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Lone wolf, maverick, member of an extremely small group of conservative <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> senators _ <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON> identifies with all those characterizations and says he does n't care as long as <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> is listening closely `` I run with a pretty small pack,'' the self-proclaimed and sole congressional spokesman for the Coalition for a Winning Ticket said late Sunday night. `` I did n't come here to blend in with the wallpaper. I'm going to compete within the bounds of civility up to the end to put forth my agenda.'' Thus far, <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON>'s effort to pressure <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> into naming a conservative running mate has attracted tremendous media coverage. <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON> planned it that way. `` If there were n't a news vacuum at this convention, we would n't really get the attention, but I saw the chance and, quite frankly, decided to exploit it,'' he said. <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON> acknowledges that all the noise wo n't win victory on the convention floor if he had to take it to a roll call vote. `` We'd be beaten,'' he said. So why fight <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> campaign attempts to create harmony? `` We're trying to sensitize him and particularly his advisers.'' <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON> said. `` <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> people are tone deaf. They are so isolated from the majority of the party.'' <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON>, 47, a former airline pilot, narrowly defeated 16-year incumbent Sen. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> McIntyre </PERSON>, a Democrat, in what was viewed as a major upset in 1978. It was <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON>'s first try for public office. He promised to be the `` toughest skinflint in the <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Senate.'' <PERSON> Humphrey </PERSON> has since carved a niche in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> as the leading spokesman against abortion. He is a fiscal conservative, strongly anti