ruit blacks and other minorities to become Republicans, but the party remains predominantly white. An <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> survey found that 92 percent of the delegates to the national convention are white. <PERSON> Du </PERSON> <PERSON> Pont </PERSON> mentioned the name of <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> just twice. Using <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>'s keep-hope-alive slogan, he said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> `` will not only keep hope alive, but he will make the dream of millions of Americans come true.'' <PERSON> Du </PERSON> <PERSON> Pont </PERSON>, a former governor of <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> and an heir to the family's chemical empire, entered the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> presidential race on Sept. 16, 1986, and dropped out last Feb. 18, two days after the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> primary.
