<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Vice President <PERSON> Salvador </PERSON> <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> began meeting opposition leaders Monday to form a new political party opposed to President <PERSON> Corazon </PERSON> <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON>, whom he accused of incompetence. Laurel met with Sen. <PERSON> Juan </PERSON> <PERSON> Ponce </PERSON> <PERSON> Enrile </PERSON>, members of ousted President <PERSON> Ferdinand </PERSON> <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON>' <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Movement </ORGANIZATION> and other opposition groups at the Club Pilipino, where Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> took her oath as president on Feb. 25, 1986. <PERSON> Enrile </PERSON> and <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> said at a news conference later that more meetings would be held to unite the opposition and seek Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON>'s ouster. `` We are just starting the evolution to unify the political parties,'' said <PERSON> Enrile </PERSON>, the only opposition member in the 23-seat <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. `` Maybe then the administration will know there is a quiet opposition strong enough to make a challenge.'' <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> said Saturday that Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> had failed to provide strong leadership in the face of the country's communist rebellion and in other economic and social crises. He urged her to step down and call new elections, and promised to resign himself if she did. If she refused, he would stay in office and join the opposition, <ORGANIZATION> Laurel </ORGANIZATION> said. <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> told reporters Monday he had not received a reply from Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> and could not say when he would formally announce an alliance with the opposition. `` I do not want to pressure Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON>,'' he added. `` The moment it becomes obvious that she will not be stepping down, I will be a free agent.'' Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> has not commented directly on <ORGA