t a year after he was overthrown in a military coup In 1979, British war hero Lord <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Mountbatten </PERSON> was killed off the coast of <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> in a boat explosion claimed by the outlawed <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>. In 1982, <PERSON> Rickey </PERSON> <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON> of the Oakland A's stole his 119th base of the season in a game against the <ORGANIZATION> Brewers </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION>, eclipsing <PERSON> Lou </PERSON> <PERSON> Brock </PERSON>'s record of 118 steals in one season. -LRB- <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON> stole three more bases the same game _ but the A's lost, 5-4. -RRB- In 1984, President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> announced a schoolteacher would be the first citizen astronaut to fly aboard the space shuttle. -LRB- <PERSON> Christa </PERSON> <PERSON> McAuliffe </PERSON> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION>, who was eventually chosen, died in the Challenger disaster in January 1986. -RRB- Ten years ago: <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> Prime Minister <PERSON> Menachem </PERSON> <PERSON> Begin </PERSON> told reporters he would enter upcoming talks with Egyptian President <PERSON> Anwar </PERSON> <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> and President <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> `` with an open mind,'' but with no changes in his <LOCATION> Mideast </LOCATION> peace plan, which called for limited Palestinian self-rule in Israeli-occupied territories. Five years ago: A quarter of a million people rallied in front of the Lincoln Memorial in the nation's capital to mark the 20th anniversary of <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Luther </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>'s `` I have a dream'' speech during the 1963 March on <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. One year ago: A Soviet Foreign Ministry official said his country was study