<SECOND>AM-Eastern Fares,0256</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eastern Slashes Some Fares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> announced Monday that it was slashing fares between <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and 16 Northeastern cities to $ 69 for the post-Labor Day season. Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s sister company under the <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> umbrella, also has announced a special $ 69 one-way fare between <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and 10 cities in the <LOCATION> Northeast </LOCATION>. The Eastern tickets, which carry a number of restrictions, went on sale Monday and will be sold through Aug. 26. The tickets apply to travel beginning Sept. 11 through Dec. 15 at savings of as much as 40 percent. <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Markesano </PERSON>, an airline analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Janney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Montgomery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Scott </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, called the move a typical seasonal promotion. `` Other airlines will have some kind of matching with similar restrictions,'' he said. <PERSON> Paula </PERSON> <PERSON> Musto </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for Eastern, said she did not expect the special fare to touch off a pricing war. `` That's not our intention,'' <PERSON> Musto </PERSON> said. `` We just want to put a good fall promotion out there.'' Eastern suffered a drop in passengers during its highly-publicized inspection by the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>, which found no important safety violations. The $ 69 fare is based on round-trip travel and applies Tuesdays through Fridays on northbound flights and Sundays through Wednesdays on southbound flights. The fare applies to travel to and from <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> cities such as <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lauderdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Orlando </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> as well as <LOCATION> Baltimore </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Buffalo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Cleveland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hartford </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Providence </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, among others.
