<HEAD>EEC Establishes Diplomatic Relations With Some COMECON Members</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION> has established formal diplomatic relations with some member nations of its Soviet bloc counterpart, <ORGANIZATION> COMECON </ORGANIZATION>, a West German official said Monday. The official, who asked not to be identified, said at least four of the <ORGANIZATION> COMECON </ORGANIZATION> countries _ the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Czechoslovakia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Bulgaria </LOCATION> _ had established formal ties with the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> and that announcements on others were expected. The other <ORGANIZATION> COMECON </ORGANIZATION> members are <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Albania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mongolia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>'s state-run <ORGANIZATION> ADN </ORGANIZATION> news agency quoted the country's foreign ministry spokesman, <PERSON> Wolfgang </PERSON> <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON>, as saying the move contributes to the creation of a `` common European house. Soviet bloc officials have used that phrase in recent weeks in calling for closer unity between <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>. Two months ago <ORGANIZATION> COMECON </ORGANIZATION>, which stands for the <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mutual </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assistance </ORGANIZATION>, and the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> paved the way for establishing formal ties by signing documents of mutual recognition. Talks between <ORGANIZATION> COMECON </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> on establishing official links began in September 1986.
